ion, after all WordPress include files and plugins have been loaded. This is very useful if your application needs to interrogate the database to modify the cache key. Activate it by setting $wp_super_cache_late_init to true in the config file.</p>\n<p>Lots to digest and new toys to try out. Hope you enjoy this new version of the plugin!</p>\n<p><strong>Related Posts</strong><ul><li><a href="http://ocaoimh.ie/wp-content/plugins/feed-statistics.php?url=aHR0cDovL29jYW9pbWguaWUvd3Atc3VwZXItY2FjaGUtMDg0LXRoZS1nYXJiYWdlLWNvbGxlY3Rvci8=" rel="">WP Super Cache 0.8.4, the garbage collector</a></li><li><a href="http://ocaoimh.ie/wp-content/plugins/feed-statistics.php?url=aHR0cDovL29jYW9pbWguaWUvd3Atc3VwZXItY2FjaGUtMDg3Lw==" rel="">WP Super Cache 0.8.7</a></li><li><a href="http://ocaoimh.ie/wp-content/plugins/feed-statistics.php?url=aHR0cDovL29jYW9pbWguaWUvd3Atc3VwZXItY2FjaGUtMC05LTUv" rel="">WP Super Cache 0.9.5</a></li></ul></p> <img src="http://ocaoimh.ie/wp-content/plugins/feed-statistics.php?view=1&post_id=89495364" width="1" height="1" />";}i:5;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:60:"Weblog Tools Collection: WordPress Plugin Releases for 10/02";s:4:"guid";s:40:"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/?p=6836";s:4:"link";s:88:"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2009/10/02/wordpress-plugin-releases-for-1002/";s:11:"description";s:2573:"<h3>New Plugins</h3>\n<p><a href="http://www.clickonf5.org/cute-profiles/">Cute Profiles</a></p>\n<p>Cute Profiles is a free Wordpress Plugin which will bring all your Social Profiles at one location i.e. either left or right side of your blog pages in a well decent floating manner, saving your sidebar or footer space for ads or other important data and widgets. Rest of the details related to features, screenshots, installation, usage and support are provided on Plugin page.</p>\n<p><a href="http://xentek.net/code/wordpress/plugins/xen-carousel/">XEN Carousel</a></p>\n<p>Call out sections of your site by easily creating a carousel of images, associated to posts or pages, for display on your home page or anywhere on your site. The carousel purposely does not come styled, but is instead semantically marked up with #IDs and .classes to make it easy for you to integrate it into your theme without much effort.</p>\n<h3>Updated Plugins</h3>\n<p><a href="http://xentek.net/code/wordpress/plugins/in-the-loop/">Be in the loop!</a></p>\n<p>Easily add any HTML, CSS, JavaScript or PHP to the beginning or end of a post. Great for when plugins forget to add this ability and you need to shoehorn a new template tag into your theme.</p>\n<p><a href="http://xentek.net/code/wordpress/plugins/flaresmith/">FlareSmith</a></p>\n<p>Integrate the FeedBurner Stats and FeedFlare services into your WordPress site &#8211; without editing your theme!</p>\n<p><a href="http://xentek.net/code/wordpress/plugins/k2-hook-up/">K2 Hook Up</a></p>\n<p>This plugin provides an options screen with each unique hook exposed as a simple text box. Insert any HTML, CSS, or JavaScript that you like, and click submit and it will be instantly published to that region of your template.</p>\n<p><a href="http://tobias.baethge.com/wordpress-plugins/wp-table-reloaded-english/">WP Table Reloaded</a></p>\n<p>This plugin enables you to create and manage tables in the admin-area of WordPress. You can then show them in your posts, on your pages or in text widgets by using a shortcode.</p>\n<p><a href="http://xentek.net/code/wordpress/plugins/wp-orphanage/">WP-Orphanage</a></p>\n<p>A Plugin to promote users with no roles set (the orphans) to the role of your choosing. Their role is upgraded when they login.</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.thunderguy.com/semicolon/wordpress/search-meter-wordpress-plugin/">Search Meter</a></p>\n<p>Search Meter is a WordPress plugin that helps you keep your blog focused on what your visitors want to read. It does this by keeping track of what your visitors are searching for.</p>";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Fri, 02 Oct 2009 20:05:44 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:7:"Perurry";}s:7:"summary";s:2573:"<h3>New Plugins</h3>\n<p><a href="http://www.clickonf5.org/cute-profiles/">Cute Profiles</a></p>\n<p>Cute Profiles is a free Wordpress Plugin which will bring all your Social Profiles at one location i.e. either left or right side of your blog pages in a well decent floating manner, saving your sidebar or footer space for ads or other important data and widgets. Rest of the details related to features, screenshots, installation, usage and support are provided on Plugin page.</p>\n<p><a href="http://xentek.net/code/wordpress/plugins/xen-carousel/">XEN Carousel</a></p>\n<p>Call out sections of your site by easily creating a carousel of images, associated to posts or pages, for display on your home page or anywhere on your site. The carousel purposely does not come styled, but is instead semantically marked up with #IDs and .classes to make it easy for you to integrate it into your theme without much effort.</p>\n<h3>Updated Plugins</h3>\n<p><a href="http://xentek.net/code/wordpress/plugins/in-the-loop/">Be in the loop!</a></p>\n<p>Easily add any HTML, CSS, JavaScript or PHP to the beginning or end of a post. Great for when plugins forget to add this ability and you need to shoehorn a new template tag into your theme.</p>\n<p><a href="http://xentek.net/code/wordpress/plugins/flaresmith/">FlareSmith</a></p>\n<p>Integrate the FeedBurner Stats and FeedFlare services into your WordPress site &#8211; without editing your theme!</p>\n<p><a href="http://xentek.net/code/wordpress/plugins/k2-hook-up/">K2 Hook Up</a></p>\n<p>This plugin provides an options screen with each unique hook exposed as a simple text box. Insert any HTML, CSS, or JavaScript that you like, and click submit and it will be instantly published to that region of your template.</p>\n<p><a href="http://tobias.baethge.com/wordpress-plugins/wp-table-reloaded-english/">WP Table Reloaded</a></p>\n<p>This plugin enables you to create and manage tables in the admin-area of WordPress. You can then show them in your posts, on your pages or in text widgets by using a shortcode.</p>\n<p><a href="http://xentek.net/code/wordpress/plugins/wp-orphanage/">WP-Orphanage</a></p>\n<p>A Plugin to promote users with no roles set (the orphans) to the role of your choosing. Their role is upgraded when they login.</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.thunderguy.com/semicolon/wordpress/search-meter-wordpress-plugin/">Search Meter</a></p>\n<p>Search Meter is a WordPress plugin that helps you keep your blog focused on what your visitors want to read. It does this by keeping track of what your visitors are searching for.</p>";}i:6;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:45:"Lloyd: Free and Open Source from the Roots Up";s:4:"guid";s:30:"http://foolswisdom.com/?p=2096";s:4:"link";s:32:"http://foolswisdom.com/roots-up/";s:11:"description";s:1798:"<blockquote><p>&#8220;<strong>Free and open source from the roots up.</strong> “Open source” can be much more than a development methodology. For me, it also constitutes a world view that upends institutionalized notions of competitive advantage that saw their apex in the twentieth century.&#8221;</p>\n<p>Excerpt from <a href="http://blog.numenity.org/">Paul Kim</a>&#8217;s &#8220;<a href="http://blog.numenity.org/2009/09/09/why-i-joined-automattic/">Why I Joined Automattic</a>&#8221; published September 9, 2009.<!-- by Paul Kim --><a href="http://blog.numenity.org/2009/09/09/why-i-joined-automattic/#comments"></a></p></blockquote>\n<div class="wp-caption alignright"><img class="  " title="Photo of Man Backflipping into Water" src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2206/2058764760_e6862d7913_m.jpg" alt="Freedom by Abnel Gonzalez, Hosted on Flickr, CC by" width="240" height="161" /><p class="wp-caption-text">Freedom by Abnel Gonzalez, CC by, Flickr Hosted</p></div>\n<p>I&#8217;ve come to think of the people who build open source and free culture into their businesses as not only having the creativity and resolve to put their values at the core of their businesses, but also the foresight and humility to know that the future is always built on the past, that the future is outside of their control, but possibly not their contribution.</p>\n<p>This is one of the main reasons I so enjoy working with <a href="http://ma.tt/">Matt Mullenweg</a>, <a href="http://toni.org/">Toni Schneider</a>, the rest of the <a href="http://automattic.com/">Automattic</a> crew, and the <a href="http://en.wordpress.com/vip-hosting/">WordPress.com VIPs</a> and <a href="http://codepoet.com/">WordPress businesses</a> I get to so regularly interact with. I&#8217;m ecstatic that Paul has joined us!</p>";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Fri, 02 Oct 2009 19:26:01 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:5:"Lloyd";}s:7:"summary";s:1798:"<blockquote><p>&#8220;<strong>Free and open source from the roots up.</strong> “Open source” can be much more than a development methodology. For me, it also constitutes a world view that upends institutionalized notions of competitive advantage that saw their apex in the twentieth century.&#8221;</p>\n<p>Excerpt from <a href="http://blog.numenity.org/">Paul Kim</a>&#8217;s &#8220;<a href="http://blog.numenity.org/2009/09/09/why-i-joined-automattic/">Why I Joined Automattic</a>&#8221; published September 9, 2009.<!-- by Paul Kim --><a href="http://blog.numenity.org/2009/09/09/why-i-joined-automattic/#comments"></a></p></blockquote>\n<div class="wp-caption alignright"><img class="  " title="Photo of Man Backflipping into Water" src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2206/2058764760_e6862d7913_m.jpg" alt="Freedom by Abnel Gonzalez, Hosted on Flickr, CC by" width="240" height="161" /><p class="wp-caption-text">Freedom by Abnel Gonzalez, CC by, Flickr Hosted</p></div>\n<p>I&#8217;ve come to think of the people who build open source and free culture into their businesses as not only having the creativity and resolve to put their values at the core of their businesses, but also the foresight and humility to know that the future is always built on the past, that the future is outside of their control, but possibly not their contribution.</p>\n<p>This is one of the main reasons I so enjoy working with <a href="http://ma.tt/">Matt Mullenweg</a>, <a href="http://toni.org/">Toni Schneider</a>, the rest of the <a href="http://automattic.com/">Automattic</a> crew, and the <a href="http://en.wordpress.com/vip-hosting/">WordPress.com VIPs</a> and <a href="http://codepoet.com/">WordPress businesses</a> I get to so regularly interact with. I&#8217;m ecstatic that Paul has joined us!</p>";}i:7;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:71:"WordPress.tv: Garron Selliken: Geotagging and Mapping WordPress Content";s:4:"guid";s:27:"http://wordpress.tv/?p=2676";s:4:"link";s:69:"http://wordpress.tv/2009/09/20/garron-selliken-geotagging-portland09/";s:11:"description";s:1386:"<div class="snap_preview"><br /><ins>\n<div class="video-player" id="x-video-10">\n </div></ins>\n<br /><a href="http://wordpress.tv/2009/09/20/garron-selliken-geotagging-portland09/"><img width="160" height="120" src="http://cdn.videos.wordpress.com/S5LxLorL/garron_768k_joe_std.original.jpg" /> </a>  <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/wptv.wordpress.com/2676/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/wptv.wordpress.com/2676/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godelicious/wptv.wordpress.com/2676/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/delicious/wptv.wordpress.com/2676/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gostumble/wptv.wordpress.com/2676/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/stumble/wptv.wordpress.com/2676/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godigg/wptv.wordpress.com/2676/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/digg/wptv.wordpress.com/2676/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/goreddit/wptv.wordpress.com/2676/"><img alt="" border="0" src="