n.videos.wordpress.com/XrmbH9m0/wordpress-langues_scruberthumbnail_0.jpg" /> </a>  <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/wptv.wordpress.com/2730/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/wptv.wordpress.com/2730/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godelicious/wptv.wordpress.com/2730/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/delicious/wptv.wordpress.com/2730/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gostumble/wptv.wordpress.com/2730/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/stumble/wptv.wordpress.com/2730/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godigg/wptv.wordpress.com/2730/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/digg/wptv.wordpress.com/2730/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/goreddit/wptv.wordpress.com/2730/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/reddit/wptv.wordpress.com/2730/" /></a> <img alt="" border="0" src="http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=wordpress.tv&blog=5089392&post=2730&subd=wptv&ref=&feed=1" /></div>";}i:11;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:52:"Weblog Tools Collection: Inject Plugin Ideas Here ->";s:4:"guid";s:40:"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/?p=6813";s:4:"link";s:78:"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2009/10/01/inject-plugin-ideas-here/";s:11:"description";s:1823:"<p>As a plugin developer I find the hardest part of the process to be coming up with new ideas that I can turn into a plugin. Sure, there are tons of places out there that list lots of ideas but, I&#8217;ve found that it&#8217;s hard to find a good idea that will actually make a useful plugin which will appeal to a large audience. Most ideas that are out there floating around are very specific and some would only be useful to only a very select few.</p>\n<p>I&#8217;ve been searching non-stop for the better part of a month now and have yet to come across an idea that would actually be very useful and also feasible. I want something that I can complete in a decent amount of time and would also leave room for lots of improvement.</p>\n<p>So, today I&#8217;m here to ask you, the user, what you want. I know this question has been asked a <strong>lot</strong> but, once more can&#8217;t hurt&#8230;</p>\n<p>What would you most love in a WordPress plugin? Is it something that should be a plugin? Or perhaps a part of the core of WordPress itself? Will many people find it useful? Or just a very select few? If such a plugin were to be created, what would you need it to do? How could it be expanded on in the future? Is it something that should remain a plugin or perhaps one day become a part of the core?</p>\n<p>So, lets hear it! Don&#8217;t hold back. Even if you don&#8217;t think it is a very good idea, I want to hear about it anyway. The best idea of the bunch will become a WordPress plugin! Any other great ideas may also eventually become a plugin. I&#8217;m all ears so let&#8217;r rip!</p>\n<p>We have a special prize for the reader whose idea we use to develop a plugin with. The reader will receive a WeblogToolsCollection hat and stickers in the mail. The winner will be announced in a subsequent post.</p>";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Thu, 01 Oct 2009 22:15:22 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:12:"James Dimick";}s:7:"summary";s:1823:"<p>As a plugin developer I find the hardest part of the process to be coming up with new ideas that I can turn into a plugin. Sure, there are tons of places out there that list lots of ideas but, I&#8217;ve found that it&#8217;s hard to find a good idea that will actually make a useful plugin which will appeal to a large audience. Most ideas that are out there floating around are very specific and some would only be useful to only a very select few.</p>\n<p>I&#8217;ve been searching non-stop for the better part of a month now and have yet to come across an idea that would actually be very useful and also feasible. I want something that I can complete in a decent amount of time and would also leave room for lots of improvement.</p>\n<p>So, today I&#8217;m here to ask you, the user, what you want. I know this question has been asked a <strong>lot</strong> but, once more can&#8217;t hurt&#8230;</p>\n<p>What would you most love in a WordPress plugin? Is it something that should be a plugin? Or perhaps a part of the core of WordPress itself? Will many people find it useful? Or just a very select few? If such a plugin were to be created, what would you need it to do? How could it be expanded on in the future? Is it something that should remain a plugin or perhaps one day become a part of the core?</p>\n<p>So, lets hear it! Don&#8217;t hold back. Even if you don&#8217;t think it is a very good idea, I want to hear about it anyway. The best idea of the bunch will become a WordPress plugin! Any other great ideas may also eventually become a plugin. I&#8217;m all ears so let&#8217;r rip!</p>\n<p>We have a special prize for the reader whose idea we use to develop a plugin with. The reader will receive a WeblogToolsCollection hat and stickers in the mail. The winner will be announced in a subsequent post.</p>";}i:12;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:62:"WordPress.tv: Will Norris: How NOT to Build a WordPress Plugin";s:4:"guid";s:27:"http://wordpress.tv/?p=2674";s:4:"link";s:71:"http://wordpress.tv/2009/09/20/will-norris-building-plugins-portland09/";s:11:"description";s:1392:"<div class="snap_preview"><br /><ins>\n<div class="video-player" id="x-video-11">\n </div></ins>\n<br /><a href="http://wordpress.tv/2009/09/20/will-norris-building-plugins-portland09/"><img width="160" height="120" src="http://cdn.videos.wordpress.com/NLDyXte5/willnorris_768k_joe_std.original.jpg" /> </a>  <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/wptv.wordpress.com/2674/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/wptv.wordpress.com/2674/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" hre